250 g Chorizo Sausage, uncased
¾ cup Basmati Rice
1 unit(s) Diced Pineapple Cup
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
7 g Cilantro
28 g Crispy Shallots
3 tbsp Guacamole
2 tbsp Chipotle Sauce
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 tsp Garlic Salt
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

To the boiling water, add rice.
Cover and reduce heat to medium-low. Cook for 12-14 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Season with salt and pepper, then fluff rice with a fork.

Meanwhile, tear cilantro.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then onions and chorizo. Cook, breaking up chorizo into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Add Mexican Seasoning and pineapple along with its juices. Cook, stirring often, until juices are absorbed, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a fork, then stir in half the crispy shallots.
Divide rice between bowls. Top with chorizo-pineapple mixture.
Drizzle with chipotle sauce.
Dollop guacamole over top.
Sprinkle with cilantro and remaining crispy shallots.